---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Stove Philosophy | Home">
  <main class="mx-auto min-h-screen max-w-5xl px-6 py-14 sm:py-20">
    <section>
      <p
        class="inline-flex rounded-full border border-amber-300/30 bg-amber-400/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium tracking-wide text-amber-200"
      >
        Stove Philosophy
      </p>
      <h1
        class="mt-5 max-w-3xl bg-gradient-to-r from-slate-100 via-cyan-100 to-indigo-200 bg-clip-text text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-transparent sm:text-6xl"
      >
        Endure heat. Stir occasionally. Pretend this is all very profound.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-base leading-7 text-slate-300 sm:text-lg">
        Stove Philosophy is the ancient art of surviving pressure with grace,
        seasoning, and just enough sarcasm to remain edible.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-12 grid gap-5 sm:grid-cols-3">
      <article
        class="rounded-xl border border-indigo-400/20 bg-gradient-to-b from-indigo-500/10 to-slate-900/70 p-5 shadow-[0_0_24px_rgba(99,102,241,0.15)]"
      >
        <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-indigo-200">Page One</p>
        <h2 class="mt-2 text-lg font-semibold text-white">Core Principles</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-300">
          Six hard truths from the stovetop, including emotional preheating and
          strategic salting.
        </p>
        <a
          href="/principles"
          class="mt-4 inline-flex text-sm font-semibold text-indigo-200 hover:text-indigo-100"
          >Read principles →</a
        >
      </article>
      <article
        class="rounded-xl border border-emerald-400/20 bg-gradient-to-b from-emerald-500/10 to-slate-900/70 p-5 shadow-[0_0_24px_rgba(16,185,129,0.15)]"
      >
        <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-emerald-200">
          Page Two
        </p>
        <h2 class="mt-2 text-lg font-semibold text-white">The Four Burners</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-300">
          A practical guide to deciding which part of life simmers while the
          others threaten mutiny.
        </p>
        <a
          href="/burners"
          class="mt-4 inline-flex text-sm font-semibold text-emerald-200 hover:text-emerald-100"
          >Balance burners →</a
        >
      </article>
      <article
        class="rounded-xl border border-amber-400/20 bg-gradient-to-b from-amber-500/10 to-slate-900/70 p-5 shadow-[0_0_24px_rgba(245,158,11,0.15)]"
      >
        <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-slate-400">
          Page Three
        </p>
        <h2 class="mt-2 text-lg font-semibold text-white">
          Leftovers & Mortality
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-300">
          A cheerful reminder that all things end, including that suspicious
          hummus in the back row.
        </p>
        <a
          href="/leftovers"
          class="mt-4 inline-flex text-sm font-semibold text-amber-200 hover:text-amber-100"
          >Contemplate leftovers →</a
        >
      </article>
    </section>

    <footer
      class="mt-14 border-t border-cyan-400/20 pt-8 text-xs text-slate-400"
    >
      © {new Date().getFullYear()} Stove Philosophy. Keep calm and lower the heat
      one notch.
    </footer>
  </main>
</Layout>
